WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:13.847 --> 00:00:17.183
♪ 'Twas down in the meadows ♪

3
00:00:17.267 --> 00:00:20.103
♪ The violets were blowing ♪

4
00:00:20.186 --> 00:00:25.775
♪ And the springtime grass
Was fresh and green ♪

5
00:00:26.359 --> 00:00:30.405
Do you think Mr. Edwards would have had
time to deliver a letter before he left?

6
00:00:30.989 --> 00:00:33.700
-Who are you writing letters to?
-No one.

7
00:00:34.951 --> 00:00:36.578
Ow.

8
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:40.248
Ma says it's because I'm sweet.

9
00:00:40.331 --> 00:00:42.625
and you're too salty
for mosquitoes to bother with.

10
00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:47.589
-I'd rather be salty than mosquito food.
-We're not supposed to go this far.

11
00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:50.717
All these bushes are loaded.

12
00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:56.681
And if we bring back enough berries
for Ma to dry. we'll have pie all winter.

13
00:00:56.765 --> 00:00:58.725
You should stop eating them. then.

14
00:01:10.570 --> 00:01:13.573
Hi! Hello! I'm Laura.

15
00:01:14.074 --> 00:01:15.074
Stop.

16
00:01:22.582 --> 00:01:24.501
I wanted to meet them.

17
00:01:24.584 --> 00:01:26.127
Ma's gonna be mad.

18
00:01:40.391 --> 00:01:41.391
Laura!

19
00:02:09.337 --> 00:02:11.673
I hope my house will look half as nice.

20
00:02:12.757 --> 00:02:13.757
It will.

21
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:16.678
Thank you. Mr. Scott.

22
00:02:17.762 --> 00:02:20.849
Who knows how long it would've taken
to finish it without your kindness.

23
00:02:21.516 --> 00:02:24.310
-Get back to work on yours tomorrow.
-Looking forward to it.

24
00:02:24.394 --> 00:02:26.479
Mr. Ingalls. Ma'am.

25
00:02:31.276 --> 00:02:33.695
Aw.

26
00:02:40.577 --> 00:02:45.373
Charles. we're not newlyweds.
We've been sleeping inside for weeks.

27
00:02:45.456 --> 00:02:47.167
It's the principle of the thing.

28
00:03:03.474 --> 00:03:04.976
It's not bad. right?

29
00:03:13.484 --> 00:03:14.736
It's perfect.

30
00:03:53.399 --> 00:03:55.526
The china shepherdess.

31
00:03:55.610 --> 00:03:56.986
That means we're home.

32
00:03:58.279 --> 00:04:00.657
Yes. Now we're home.

33
00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:04.452
Safe and sound.

34
00:04:10.166 --> 00:04:12.206
♪ The fox went out
On a chilly night ♪

35
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:14.045
♪ He prayed to the Moon
To give him light ♪

36
00:04:14.128 --> 00:04:17.799
♪ For a many a mile to go that night
Before he reached the town-o ♪

37
00:04:17.882 --> 00:04:19.884
♪ Town-o. town-o ♪

38
00:04:19.968 --> 00:04:24.639
♪ Many a mile to go that night
Before he reached the town-o ♪

39
00:04:27.725 --> 00:04:28.893
Is it a present?

40
00:04:29.602 --> 00:04:32.021
-What?
-The surprise in town.

41
00:04:32.105 --> 00:04:35.149
It's the post office.
The new post office is the surprise.

42
00:04:35.233 --> 00:04:38.403
It's not a surprise
if you already know about it.

43
00:04:38.903 --> 00:04:42.323
-Pa said there was a surprise.
-Did I say something about a surprise?

44
00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:15.481
Everything's fine.

45
00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:38.713
Want a cookie? Here you go.

46
00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:46.345
Ah.

47
00:05:46.387 --> 00:05:47.764
Well done. Mr. Ingalls.

48
00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:49.223
-Thank you.
-Well done.

49
00:05:49.724 --> 00:05:50.724
Beautiful work.

50
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:52.310
-Thanks.
-Great stuff.

51
00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:54.187
Ah. Jacob.

52
00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:56.898
Pa. did you draw this?

53
00:05:57.899 --> 00:06:00.443
-I just might've.
-You're full of surprises.

54
00:06:00.526 --> 00:06:02.236
Aren't I?

55
00:06:06.657 --> 00:06:08.201
Mr. Ingalls.

56
00:06:08.951 --> 00:06:10.453
These must be your girls.

57
00:06:10.536 --> 00:06:13.414
Nice to see you. Miss Aubert.
This is Caroline. my wife.

58
00:06:14.832 --> 00:06:17.835
-Our daughters. Mary and Laura.
-Pleased to meet you all.

59
00:06:21.005 --> 00:06:23.508
I didn't know ladies could wear trousers.

60
00:06:23.591 --> 00:06:26.594
Well. most people don't consider me
to be much of a lady.

61
00:06:29.138 --> 00:06:30.181
Caroline.

62
00:06:30.681 --> 00:06:33.393
Let's get you a spot
up front for Eli's speech.

63
00:06:33.476 --> 00:06:36.396
And let's get your girls a cookie
before mine gobble them all up.

64
00:06:41.692 --> 00:06:43.736
If you see Edwards.
will you give him my best?

65
00:06:48.032 --> 00:06:50.326
Gather round. folks. Gather round.

66
00:06:54.372 --> 00:06:56.124
The post office

67
00:06:57.208 --> 00:07:00.461
is the lifeblood of the American West.

68
00:07:00.545 --> 00:07:02.839
Part of what gives us our strength.

69
00:07:02.922 --> 00:07:05.758
so far from everything we've ever known.

70
00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:07.135
is the knowledge

71
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:10.555
that our families can send word.

72
00:07:10.638 --> 00:07:13.391
This post office will be a beacon!

73
00:07:13.891 --> 00:07:18.104
It will bring
the wider world to Independence.

74
00:07:19.480 --> 00:07:26.028
Next up. more settlers. more prosperity.
and maybe even a railroad line.

75
00:07:30.408 --> 00:07:34.078
The Independence post office is now open!

76
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:54.557
Very exciting.

77
00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:57.226
Laura and Mary.
a letter from Grandma to both of you.

78
00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:00.438
-Careful.
-Caroline. a letter from Eliza.

79
00:08:00.938 --> 00:08:04.192
For me. mortgage payments
from Mr. Gustafson.

80
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:07.069
-You're gonna ruin it.
-Laura.

81
00:08:07.778 --> 00:08:09.071
Mary gets to read it first.

82
00:08:09.155 --> 00:08:12.158
seeing as you took the liberty
of tearing it open like a baby goat.

83
00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:14.790
Those two are gonna snip and snap
at each other

84
00:08:14.827 --> 00:08:16.867
until we find them
some other children to play with.

85
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:25.004
-What is it?
-Bad.

86
00:08:25.505 --> 00:08:29.383
Gustafson says my father's been holed up
in the house. not accepting visitors.

87
00:08:30.593 --> 00:08:32.553
Making Peter work the farm all alone.

88
00:08:33.638 --> 00:08:35.014
He hasn't even been to church.

89
00:08:35.097 --> 00:08:38.226
It's the grief.
He'll come through it in time.

90
00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:40.603
I was hoping he would write.

91
00:08:41.896 --> 00:08:43.564
-I shouldn't have.
-Charles…

92
00:08:45.733 --> 00:08:46.733
It wasn't your fault.

93
00:08:47.276 --> 00:08:49.716
Your father knows that.
He's just not willing to admit it yet.

94
00:08:50.279 --> 00:08:52.865
He's stubborn. like his son.

95
00:09:03.042 --> 00:09:04.043
Sit in the shade.

96
00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:07.838
We got a pocketful of cash
and a long list of supplies to buy.

97
00:09:08.339 --> 00:09:10.424
-Don't forget the slate and pencil.
-I won't.

98
00:09:10.925 --> 00:09:12.260
And not too much candy.

99
00:09:38.452 --> 00:09:39.452
Sorry.

100
00:09:40.705 --> 00:09:43.708
-I can help you read it if you want.
-I don't need any help.

101
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:45.918
Fine.

102
00:09:47.044 --> 00:09:49.839
Your ma's reading and resting.
so we're gonna do the shopping.

103
00:09:50.881 --> 00:09:53.676
-Know what that means?
-Treats!

104
00:10:05.479 --> 00:10:07.898
Go ahead. Stay close.

105
00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:13.404
-Did you get a cookie?
-I already ate mine.

106
00:10:13.487 --> 00:10:15.448
Me too. I love frosting.

107
00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:19.785
I saw some Osage girls down by the creek.
They were picking blackberries.

108
00:10:19.869 --> 00:10:22.705
How do you say hi in Osage
so I can say hi next time?

109
00:10:25.666 --> 00:10:28.336
You should come see the kittens again.
They're getting all fluffy.

110
00:10:28.419 --> 00:10:30.796
Mama said I had to give one away.
Then she forgot.

111
00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:39.639
-And this.
-Thank you.

112
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:50.399
Now that we're settled.
Ma says that we have to start lessons.

113
00:10:50.941 --> 00:10:52.318
And she won't forget.

114
00:10:53.944 --> 00:10:56.322
You're going to school? Where?

115
00:10:56.405 --> 00:10:57.490
Nowhere.

116
00:10:58.324 --> 00:10:59.325
Just at home.

117
00:11:00.284 --> 00:11:02.620
Ma was a teacher before she married Pa.

118
00:11:03.621 --> 00:11:04.955
You don't like school?

119
00:11:05.539 --> 00:11:07.750
I just think there are
better things to do.

120
00:11:09.543 --> 00:11:13.547
like hunting and fishing

121
00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:16.133
and collecting rocks
and playing with Jack.

122
00:11:17.343 --> 00:11:21.013
Back in Wisconsin.
at least there was recess with other kids.

123
00:11:21.931 --> 00:11:24.850
Now it's just gonna be me and Mary

124
00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:29.897
and spelling words and poems
in that dumb old grammar book.

125
00:11:30.898 --> 00:11:32.191
I love poems.

126
00:11:32.274 --> 00:11:35.611
And I've always wanted to go to school
in St. Paul where Mama and Father went.

127
00:11:37.405 --> 00:11:39.448
You should come do school with us.

128
00:11:40.032 --> 00:11:41.033
Really?

129
00:11:41.117 --> 00:11:44.120
School would be so much better
with you and not just Mary.

130
00:11:46.622 --> 00:11:47.748
You ready to go?

131
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:50.593
Could I take lessons
with Laura?

132
00:11:50.668 --> 00:11:54.338
Mrs. Ingalls is a real teacher.
and she's teaching them at home.

133
00:11:55.631 --> 00:11:57.133
We'll have to ask your mother.

134
00:12:09.270 --> 00:12:12.690
Good afternoon. Dr. Tann.
Got your order right here.

135
00:12:12.773 --> 00:12:13.773
Ah. thank you.

136
00:12:16.110 --> 00:12:18.988
I am curious about some
of the items on that shelf.

137
00:12:19.071 --> 00:12:19.905
Oh.

138
00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:23.242
-Okay.
-Wow. The bird skeleton in particular.

139
00:12:24.618 --> 00:12:28.539
It's not exactly the kind of thing
you expect to find in a general store.

140
00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:33.169
Told my sister she'd be scaring off
business with that kinda nonsense.

141
00:12:33.252 --> 00:12:38.174
I doubt it'll sell. but I couldn't resist.
I've always been interested in anatomy.

142
00:12:39.675 --> 00:12:42.386
-The sciences. in general. I mean.
-Yeah.

143
00:12:44.096 --> 00:12:46.098
-News from home?
-Oh. uh…

144
00:12:46.182 --> 00:12:50.811
No. This is. uh. word of an intermittent
fever outbreak in Oswego.

145
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:53.022
We'll need some quinine
if it makes its way out here.

146
00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:53.939
How's your stock?

147
00:12:54.023 --> 00:12:57.276
I'll have to check. but anything
I have is yours for the taking.

148
00:12:58.360 --> 00:12:59.904
I'll keep that in mind.

149
00:13:23.803 --> 00:13:25.429
-Thinking about spring planting?
-Hm.

150
00:13:25.513 --> 00:13:26.597
Corn. potatoes…

151
00:13:26.680 --> 00:13:30.559
Peas do well out here.
Squash. greens of all kinds. rosemary.

152
00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:34.188
And the flowers. it's…
They're like something out of a dream.

153
00:13:34.271 --> 00:13:36.649
Caroline's kitchen gardens
are a thing of beauty.

154
00:13:36.732 --> 00:13:39.568
-Everyone says so.
-I'll get going on your order.

155
00:13:39.652 --> 00:13:40.652
Thank you.

156
00:13:51.747 --> 00:13:53.165
Treats.

157
00:13:53.999 --> 00:13:55.668
You'll share with your sister?

158
00:13:59.255 --> 00:14:00.381
I'll share.

159
00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:07.972
Hi. Caleb.

160
00:14:09.139 --> 00:14:11.892
I… I was wondering
if you got the letter I sent?

161
00:14:11.976 --> 00:14:14.311
Mr. Edwards was supposed to deliver it.

162
00:14:18.691 --> 00:14:19.817
Well?

163
00:14:24.822 --> 00:14:27.116
I don't wanna talk to a boy
with no manners anyway.

164
00:14:27.199 --> 00:14:28.199
Mary.

165
00:14:29.159 --> 00:14:30.703
That's not how we talk to people.

166
00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:32.788
Let's go find your ma.

167
00:14:40.212 --> 00:14:41.297
Dearest Caroline.

168
00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:45.467
I can't bear to think of you so far
from home on such a foolish adventure.

169
00:14:45.968 --> 00:14:48.095
If you have any sense at all.

170
00:14:48.178 --> 00:14:51.640
you'll bring the girls back
to Wisconsin and have the baby here.

171
00:14:54.476 --> 00:14:56.020
What's the word from home?

172
00:14:58.480 --> 00:15:00.024
Eliza sends her love.

173
00:15:01.066 --> 00:15:02.066
She does?

174
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:04.236
Doesn't sound like her.

175
00:15:11.493 --> 00:15:12.703
Everything all right?

176
00:15:14.371 --> 00:15:15.873
Just the heat of the day.

177
00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:19.126
Let's get you home. then. Let's go.

178
00:15:28.344 --> 00:15:30.596
What did he do to make you so mad?

179
00:15:32.389 --> 00:15:34.516
You can have it. I'm not hungry.

180
00:16:03.462 --> 00:16:04.713
It's so early.

181
00:16:06.799 --> 00:16:09.343
Mr. Scott and I wanna
finish his house by week's end.

182
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:11.720
I could come help.

183
00:16:12.638 --> 00:16:15.182
I could sand corners or hold nails.

184
00:16:15.265 --> 00:16:19.436
And I could teach Mr. Scott more songs.
He hardly knows any good ones.

185
00:16:20.270 --> 00:16:21.563
But you have lessons.

186
00:16:22.314 --> 00:16:26.151
I hate being inside all day
when the prairie is right out here.

187
00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:29.738
What am I ever going to need in a book?

188
00:16:31.156 --> 00:16:33.158
Books help you know
about the whole wide world.

189
00:16:34.076 --> 00:16:35.577
Not just Wisconsin.

190
00:16:36.203 --> 00:16:37.705
Not just the prairie.

191
00:16:37.788 --> 00:16:39.456
All kinds of places.

192
00:16:40.332 --> 00:16:41.542
All kinds of people.

193
00:16:42.042 --> 00:16:44.128
Could you take me to meet the Osage. then?

194
00:16:45.629 --> 00:16:47.673
We could ride out
to the camp and say hello.

195
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:53.095
Ma says they're leaving soon.
and I don't wanna miss my chance.

196
00:16:56.473 --> 00:16:57.473
We'll see.

197
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:13.032
"Long lines of cliff".

198
00:17:13.991 --> 00:17:20.748
"Breaking have left a cha…."

199
00:17:20.831 --> 00:17:21.831
Chasm.

200
00:17:22.374 --> 00:17:24.376
Mary. please.

201
00:17:29.965 --> 00:17:31.759
You know who loves poems?

202
00:17:32.843 --> 00:17:33.843
Good Eagle.

203
00:17:33.886 --> 00:17:35.179
So you've mentioned.

204
00:17:35.262 --> 00:17:37.598
I'd probably learn a lot faster
if she were here.

205
00:17:38.640 --> 00:17:41.727
Because she would help me. unlike Mary.

206
00:17:42.478 --> 00:17:43.562
who only makes fun.

207
00:17:43.645 --> 00:17:47.900
Someone as slow as you
would try anyone's P-A-T-I-E-N-C-E.

208
00:17:49.151 --> 00:17:51.612
That spells patience.
in case you didn't know.

209
00:17:53.655 --> 00:17:56.408
That's water all over your dress.
in case you didn't know.

210
00:17:56.492 --> 00:17:58.869
That's enough.
If you're uninterested in lessons.

211
00:17:58.952 --> 00:18:02.706
you can get interested in chores.
Laura. go to the creek and get some water.

212
00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:04.893
-Mary. sweep the floors.
-You swept them this morning.

213
00:18:04.917 --> 00:18:07.836
-Sweep them again.
-She likes going down to the river.

214
00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:09.588
It's not even a punishment.

215
00:18:20.224 --> 00:18:21.224
Hey.

216
00:18:21.934 --> 00:18:23.435
What has gotten into you?

217
00:18:23.519 --> 00:18:26.105
I'm tired of having to share
everything with her.

218
00:18:27.397 --> 00:18:31.360
Candy. lessons. letters. and a bed.

219
00:18:32.402 --> 00:18:35.447
Why can't I have anything of my own?

220
00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:37.949
Oh…

221
00:18:39.284 --> 00:18:42.621
Once your brother is born.
there'll be a lot more sharing to do.

222
00:18:43.205 --> 00:18:45.040
I suggest you make peace with it.

223
00:18:48.335 --> 00:18:49.335
Yes. Ma.

224
00:19:11.358 --> 00:19:13.443
If you have any sense at all.

225
00:19:13.527 --> 00:19:17.030
you'll bring the girls back
to Wisconsin and have the baby here.

226
00:19:17.114 --> 00:19:20.033
I'll send money for tickets
just as soon as I have it.

227
00:19:20.117 --> 00:19:22.661
Peter isn't ready to forgive Charles yet.

228
00:19:22.744 --> 00:19:25.998
but you and the girls
will be welcomed with open arms.

229
00:19:52.608 --> 00:19:54.735
Got a letter from my cousin yesterday.

230
00:19:55.402 --> 00:19:57.404
He came out west
with me to build this place.

231
00:19:57.487 --> 00:19:59.156
but our grandfather didn't approve.

232
00:19:59.239 --> 00:20:02.284
so he bent like a reed
and went running back to Boston.

233
00:20:02.367 --> 00:20:03.452
But not you.

234
00:20:03.535 --> 00:20:06.121
I wanted to see what it'd be like
to do something on my own.

235
00:20:06.914 --> 00:20:12.586
Find a new home. new way to be.
new people. new skies. new girls.

236
00:20:21.803 --> 00:20:23.722
I couldn't bear to pin it
at the hotel.

237
00:20:24.389 --> 00:20:25.432
Me neither.

238
00:20:26.725 --> 00:20:29.311
Anyway. my family
hasn't cut me off yet.

239
00:20:31.355 --> 00:20:33.023
What do you know about Lacey Aubert?

240
00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:36.610
I know your grandfather wouldn't approve.

241
00:20:37.736 --> 00:20:38.946
I guess he wouldn't.

242
00:20:40.155 --> 00:20:41.573
She's awfully pretty though.

243
00:20:43.033 --> 00:20:44.284
Scott. Ingalls.

244
00:20:44.368 --> 00:20:45.577
Hello.

245
00:20:46.328 --> 00:20:49.289
Mr. James. What brings you out?

246
00:20:50.165 --> 00:20:53.752
I heard Mr. Ingalls was helping you
with the house. so I thought I'd ride out.

247
00:20:56.588 --> 00:20:59.216
I'm. uh. actually here to talk to you

248
00:20:59.299 --> 00:21:02.010
about a community project
I'd like your help with.

249
00:21:02.803 --> 00:21:04.054
Another postcard?

250
00:21:04.137 --> 00:21:05.180
A church.

251
00:21:05.681 --> 00:21:07.391
I've been promising Jemma for ages.

252
00:21:07.474 --> 00:21:10.978
but I hadn't found a draftsman
or a carpenter I trusted

253
00:21:11.061 --> 00:21:12.938
until you came along.

254
00:21:13.021 --> 00:21:15.607
Are you interested
in giving our community a boost?

255
00:21:15.691 --> 00:21:18.694
Now. I'd provide the materials.
of course. and the volunteers.

256
00:21:19.653 --> 00:21:20.570
I'd be honored.

257
00:21:21.989 --> 00:21:24.032
Good man. Good man.

258
00:21:26.743 --> 00:21:29.621
These cursed little vipers
are everywhere.

259
00:21:29.705 --> 00:21:31.999
Does this mean
we're finally getting a land office?

260
00:21:32.082 --> 00:21:34.376
I mean. post office here
and a church on the way.

261
00:21:37.838 --> 00:21:39.381
This place is special.

262
00:21:41.049 --> 00:21:44.136
I came here to scout for the railroad.
and I tell ya…

263
00:21:45.262 --> 00:21:46.596
…I fell in love.

264
00:21:47.264 --> 00:21:50.517
I bought the land for the town
of Independence from the Osage myself.

265
00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:54.438
And that purchase taught me
everything I need to know about the Osage.

266
00:21:54.521 --> 00:21:57.357
-Which is?
-They're a reasonable people.

267
00:21:57.441 --> 00:21:58.275
They like trade.

268
00:21:58.358 --> 00:22:03.238
and they have the good sense to hear
the sweet sounds of progress coming west.

269
00:22:03.322 --> 00:22:05.115
So they will sell to the government?

270
00:22:05.198 --> 00:22:06.491
You know as well as I do

271
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:09.536
that molasses would beat
the US government in a footrace.

272
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:14.333
But they'll make the Osage
a fair offer for the rest of this land.

273
00:22:14.416 --> 00:22:16.168
and the Osage will sell.

274
00:22:16.251 --> 00:22:18.253
just like they sold to me.

275
00:22:18.337 --> 00:22:22.132
And once they do. you'll each have
a claim on this land you're proving up.

276
00:22:24.092 --> 00:22:26.132
I was beginning to worry
about what to tell Caroline

277
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:27.418
if things weren't settled soon.

278
00:22:27.471 --> 00:22:30.766
Give it a month or two.
and all will be as right as rain.

279
00:22:31.850 --> 00:22:33.810
Have faith. Mr. Ingalls.

280
00:22:34.770 --> 00:22:35.604
Have faith.

281
00:22:42.361 --> 00:22:44.654
Look. Jack! They took the flowers!

282
00:22:51.620 --> 00:22:53.663
Everyone likes gumdrops. right?

283
00:23:00.128 --> 00:23:01.838
Come on. Jack!

284
00:23:29.950 --> 00:23:30.992
He likes you.

285
00:23:34.663 --> 00:23:35.664
Hello.

286
00:23:38.500 --> 00:23:41.002
My friend Good Eagle
taught me that.

287
00:23:42.170 --> 00:23:43.547
Do you know Good Eagle?

288
00:23:52.055 --> 00:23:52.889
I'm Laura.

289
00:23:52.973 --> 00:23:54.015
No.

290
00:23:57.602 --> 00:23:59.688
-Would you like some cornbread?
-Laura.

291
00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:03.066
It's okay. Ma.

292
00:24:03.692 --> 00:24:04.818
I'll get it.

293
00:24:38.018 --> 00:24:40.395
One of those was for me.

294
00:24:43.398 --> 00:24:45.775
I could make coffee or tea.

295
00:24:47.152 --> 00:24:48.528
Take whatever you want and go.

296
00:24:50.572 --> 00:24:51.698
Mm.

297
00:24:59.498 --> 00:25:01.791
You're being greedy.

298
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:04.961
She said take whatever we want.

299
00:25:05.045 --> 00:25:08.465
I doubt she meant all their food.

300
00:25:08.548 --> 00:25:13.929
These people moved into our land.

301
00:25:14.012 --> 00:25:17.432
built a house with our trees.

302
00:25:17.516 --> 00:25:20.352
offered us jam

303
00:25:20.435 --> 00:25:25.065
made from our blackberries.

304
00:25:26.233 --> 00:25:28.610
You call it greedy.

305
00:25:29.194 --> 00:25:31.404
I call it fair.

306
00:25:35.784 --> 00:25:37.661
Jack. don't beg.

307
00:25:37.744 --> 00:25:41.414
We have a story about dogs.

308
00:25:41.998 --> 00:25:46.211
how they help us be
the best version of ourselves.

309
00:25:48.296 --> 00:25:49.923
Jack's a good dog.

310
00:25:51.591 --> 00:25:52.591
a good friend.

311
00:25:56.471 --> 00:25:59.391
That's enough. Let's go.

312
00:26:07.566 --> 00:26:10.110
That's Ma's.

313
00:26:11.194 --> 00:26:13.446
-You can't take her doll.
-Let them go.

314
00:26:32.215 --> 00:26:33.300
Everything's fine.

315
00:26:36.094 --> 00:26:37.262
Everything's fine.

316
00:26:43.518 --> 00:26:44.518
Hey. Caroline!

317
00:26:45.020 --> 00:26:48.023
You'll never guess what's finally
coming to town and who's gonna build it.

318
00:26:57.657 --> 00:26:58.825
Caroline?

319
00:26:59.409 --> 00:27:01.119
Caroline?

320
00:27:05.749 --> 00:27:09.544
-What's wrong? What happened?
-Two Osage men came into the house.

321
00:27:10.045 --> 00:27:12.172
They took all of our food and your tobacco

322
00:27:13.089 --> 00:27:14.299
and Ma's china doll.

323
00:27:17.302 --> 00:27:19.763
-Are you all right?
-They didn't hurt us.

324
00:27:20.847 --> 00:27:21.847
Laura?

325
00:27:23.183 --> 00:27:24.183
I'm fine.

326
00:27:35.487 --> 00:27:36.487
Okay.

327
00:27:48.249 --> 00:27:50.919
She was the last thing
my father ever gave me.

328
00:27:53.922 --> 00:27:56.257
Eliza said she would break
on the way here.

329
00:27:57.133 --> 00:27:58.218
But she made it.

330
00:27:59.928 --> 00:28:01.054
A miracle.

331
00:28:03.473 --> 00:28:05.684
It was like Father
was right there with us.

332
00:28:06.726 --> 00:28:07.977
keeping her safe…

333
00:28:10.188 --> 00:28:11.189
Keeping me safe.

334
00:28:12.899 --> 00:28:14.025
And now she's gone.

335
00:28:14.609 --> 00:28:15.443
I'm sorry.

336
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.127
This house was supposed to keep us safe.

337
00:28:17.195 --> 00:28:19.656
-It will.
-You said they were leaving.

338
00:28:22.200 --> 00:28:24.744
-It won't happen again. I promise.
-How can you promise that?

339
00:28:24.828 --> 00:28:26.371
I'll talk to Mitchell.

340
00:28:26.454 --> 00:28:27.914
What's he gonna do about it?

341
00:28:31.543 --> 00:28:33.002
I will find a way to fix this.

342
00:28:52.480 --> 00:28:54.542
Are you gonna tell me
what Father Schoenmakers wrote.

343
00:28:54.566 --> 00:28:56.606
Or are you gonna read that thing
over and over again

344
00:28:56.651 --> 00:28:58.653
like one of those terrible
dime novels you love?

345
00:28:59.487 --> 00:29:00.488
She…

346
00:29:01.281 --> 00:29:04.534
He wants to introduce me
to the new Indian agent.

347
00:29:05.034 --> 00:29:06.034
Isaac Gibson.

348
00:29:06.786 --> 00:29:07.786
Why?

349
00:29:08.496 --> 00:29:10.999
Some kind of translating job.

350
00:29:12.292 --> 00:29:16.212
He also said a spot opened up
for Good Eagle if we still wanna send her.

351
00:29:17.130 --> 00:29:20.383
I think it would be a good idea for her
to go to school with other children.

352
00:29:20.467 --> 00:29:22.427
make some friends other than her cousins.

353
00:29:22.510 --> 00:29:26.097
I don't want her away from home right now.
I want her close.

354
00:29:26.681 --> 00:29:28.141
I want her safe.

355
00:29:29.392 --> 00:29:31.603
She asked if she could study
with the Ingalls girls.

356
00:29:31.686 --> 00:29:35.523
Down the road.
maybe one or two days a week.

357
00:29:35.607 --> 00:29:39.694
Absolutely not. Who knows
what kind of nonsense they'd teach her.

358
00:29:42.864 --> 00:29:44.991
I bring gifts.

359
00:29:45.074 --> 00:29:47.114
Usually you just bring
an empty stomach.

360
00:29:47.160 --> 00:29:50.413
Not this time. sister.

361
00:29:51.956 --> 00:29:55.335
You don't like coffee.

362
00:29:55.835 --> 00:29:58.588
That's why I brought it to you.

363
00:30:03.384 --> 00:30:07.138
Myron and I were having
some fun with the settlers on the ridge.

364
00:30:07.972 --> 00:30:10.600
-What settlers?
-Woman and a couple of kids.

365
00:30:10.683 --> 00:30:12.352
One of 'em said she knew Good Eagle.

366
00:30:15.730 --> 00:30:17.023
What were you thinking?

367
00:30:17.690 --> 00:30:20.693
I was thinking there's a post office
opening up in town.

368
00:30:21.861 --> 00:30:24.197
which means those settlers
are gonna keep coming.

369
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:29.118
What do you care?
You don't like the settlers either.

370
00:30:29.202 --> 00:30:34.040
No. but I have the good sense not to
harass a woman at home with her children.

371
00:30:34.624 --> 00:30:35.542
Nothing happened.

372
00:30:35.625 --> 00:30:38.336
No. but it could have.
What if she had a weapon?

373
00:30:38.419 --> 00:30:41.673
What if her husband had come home?
You could have ended up dead!

374
00:30:41.756 --> 00:30:42.756
And for what?

375
00:30:42.799 --> 00:30:44.259
Foolishness!

376
00:30:45.051 --> 00:30:47.846
-It was Myron's idea.
-Of course it was.

377
00:30:47.929 --> 00:30:49.222
I thought…

378
00:30:51.683 --> 00:30:53.101
Good Eagle might like this.

379
00:30:55.979 --> 00:30:57.856
That's not yours to give.

380
00:31:15.748 --> 00:31:16.748
Come on in.

381
00:31:33.766 --> 00:31:34.809
Caroline?

382
00:31:36.978 --> 00:31:38.897
Poor dear. What happened?

383
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:42.817
Ugh.

384
00:31:42.901 --> 00:31:44.694
And in your own home.

385
00:31:45.528 --> 00:31:46.613
It's too much.

386
00:31:47.196 --> 00:31:48.448
They didn't hurt us.

387
00:31:51.868 --> 00:31:56.915
It's all well and good to have compassion.
young lady. but there are limits.

388
00:31:58.041 --> 00:32:01.586
I've seen things no human being
should ever have to witness.

389
00:32:02.712 --> 00:32:04.923
Back in Minnesota. the Dakota War…

390
00:32:05.006 --> 00:32:08.301
Caroline. you were close enough.
You know how it was.

391
00:32:08.384 --> 00:32:10.678
Once you've lived through a massacre…

392
00:32:10.762 --> 00:32:12.639
-What's a massacre?
-Never mind.

393
00:32:15.183 --> 00:32:16.183
Girls.

394
00:32:17.143 --> 00:32:18.019
go outside.

395
00:32:18.102 --> 00:32:21.147
Sit on the front steps with Jack.
Close the door behind you.

396
00:32:25.610 --> 00:32:26.486
You too. Mary.

397
00:32:26.569 --> 00:32:29.948
-I'm old enough to listen.
-Go outside with your sister.

398
00:32:37.246 --> 00:32:38.122
Mary?

399
00:32:39.457 --> 00:32:41.709
-Where are you going?
-Don't follow me.

400
00:32:49.342 --> 00:32:52.762
They came in my house and took everything.
My wife and daughters were all alone.

401
00:32:52.845 --> 00:32:55.098
And if that's not a threat.
I'm not sure what is.

402
00:32:55.765 --> 00:33:01.771
Some of the young men. they… like to
collect a kind of rent from the settlers.

403
00:33:02.563 --> 00:33:03.563
Rent?

404
00:33:03.606 --> 00:33:05.316
They feel we're owed.

405
00:33:06.609 --> 00:33:07.902
Do you feel that way too?

406
00:33:07.986 --> 00:33:09.195
They're frustrated.

407
00:33:09.779 --> 00:33:10.905
They're angry.

408
00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:16.577
They've lost a way of life.
They've lost a sense of purpose.

409
00:33:17.787 --> 00:33:19.330
I understand that loss.

410
00:33:21.165 --> 00:33:23.668
I can't have strangers
walking into my house uninvited.

411
00:33:23.751 --> 00:33:25.628
I think they'd say the same thing.

412
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:33.260
Is there a way…

413
00:33:35.179 --> 00:33:38.766
That I could pay this rent in advance?

414
00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:40.935
I don't think that's really the point.

415
00:33:43.896 --> 00:33:48.526
This morning. Eli James made it sound like
the land deal was over but the shouting...

416
00:33:48.609 --> 00:33:49.861
Eli James.

417
00:33:50.737 --> 00:33:53.617
Now you're making it seem like
I'll never be able to call my home my own.

418
00:33:53.698 --> 00:33:56.951
I'd be careful what I believed
from a railroad man.

419
00:33:58.036 --> 00:34:01.831
The fact is this is still Osage land.

420
00:34:03.207 --> 00:34:05.918
The railroad made a deal.
Congress scuttled it.

421
00:34:06.002 --> 00:34:08.004
and now everything's back in play.

422
00:34:10.006 --> 00:34:11.299
So there's no deal coming.

423
00:34:11.382 --> 00:34:15.094
Believe me. we all want this settled
just as much as you do.

424
00:34:16.971 --> 00:34:18.765
If the government makes an offer.

425
00:34:18.848 --> 00:34:22.769
we'll decide if we can live with it.
if we wanna live with it.

426
00:34:24.228 --> 00:34:27.899
But until then. we're all in limbo.

427
00:34:30.318 --> 00:34:32.403
I promised my wife she'd be safe.

428
00:34:33.237 --> 00:34:35.156
She's as safe as any of us are.

429
00:34:40.244 --> 00:34:44.415
We can tell her those two men
won't come to her house again.

430
00:35:10.733 --> 00:35:11.776
Hi. Mary.

431
00:35:15.947 --> 00:35:19.283
I didn't mean to run away the other day.

432
00:35:19.992 --> 00:35:24.330
I'm… I'm just not good with words. I…

433
00:35:25.081 --> 00:35:29.335
I… I think about what I wanna say.
and… I don't really know how to say it.

434
00:35:29.418 --> 00:35:34.006
so it's kinda just easier
not to say anything at all.

435
00:35:44.100 --> 00:35:45.601
I'm glad you wrote me though.

436
00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:49.730
I wrote you back. actually.

437
00:35:54.068 --> 00:35:55.068
Here you go.

438
00:35:56.070 --> 00:35:57.070
Thank you.

439
00:35:59.866 --> 00:36:02.410
Oh. no. no.
You don't have to read it right now.

440
00:36:08.958 --> 00:36:10.668
I'm sorry I was rude yesterday.

441
00:36:11.961 --> 00:36:12.961
I didn't mind.

442
00:36:16.382 --> 00:36:18.926
Uh. I guess I'll run
these packages up to the house. then.

443
00:36:19.010 --> 00:36:22.180
-No. It… it's okay. I can take them.
-Okay.

444
00:36:23.598 --> 00:36:26.142
I'd just rather have something for myself.

445
00:36:26.893 --> 00:36:27.893
A friend.

446
00:36:29.103 --> 00:36:31.314
I mean. if you wanna be friends?

447
00:36:31.981 --> 00:36:33.357
Yeah. Yeah. I do.

448
00:37:08.059 --> 00:37:09.268
What's on your mind?

449
00:37:15.441 --> 00:37:19.487
The other day.
I saw some Osage girls at the creek…

450
00:37:23.324 --> 00:37:26.035
So I left them some flowers.

451
00:37:28.246 --> 00:37:29.914
And then I went back.

452
00:37:30.414 --> 00:37:32.708
and I left them some gumdrops

453
00:37:33.709 --> 00:37:34.835
as a present.

454
00:37:37.797 --> 00:37:38.797
I see.

455
00:37:40.174 --> 00:37:43.052
But then those men came into the house…

456
00:37:46.097 --> 00:37:47.640
And they took the doll…

457
00:37:49.642 --> 00:37:51.102
And all our food.

458
00:37:53.396 --> 00:37:56.607
And now Mrs. James says
there's going to be a massacre.

459
00:37:58.734 --> 00:38:00.736
There's not gonna be any massacre.

460
00:38:02.947 --> 00:38:04.573
None of this is your fault.

461
00:38:05.366 --> 00:38:07.201
Your ma and Mrs. James…

462
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:13.416
They worry because bad things
happened a long time ago.

463
00:38:14.792 --> 00:38:16.711
when you were too little to remember.

464
00:38:17.878 --> 00:38:18.878
The war?

465
00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:20.256
Yes.

466
00:38:20.339 --> 00:38:22.216
But this is a different place

467
00:38:23.426 --> 00:38:24.593
with different people.

468
00:38:27.263 --> 00:38:29.473
I didn't mean to upset Ma.

469
00:38:32.059 --> 00:38:33.894
I just wanted to make friends.

470
00:38:37.231 --> 00:38:38.774
You have a curious heart.

471
00:38:40.985 --> 00:38:43.237
An open heart. It's a good thing.

472
00:38:43.821 --> 00:38:45.781
Just remember to be careful with it.

473
00:39:38.334 --> 00:39:40.878
I got the coffee too.
but the rest we'll have to replace.

474
00:39:57.311 --> 00:39:59.397
This is their land. isn't it?

475
00:40:01.524 --> 00:40:02.524
The Osages'.

476
00:40:11.784 --> 00:40:15.913
Jemma told me all about it. I assume
you've known for quite some time.

477
00:40:20.876 --> 00:40:22.420
I didn't wanna worry you.

478
00:40:22.503 --> 00:40:25.089
I'm not a child.

479
00:40:28.050 --> 00:40:32.388
I deserve to know where we stand out here.
what our life is going to look like.

480
00:40:32.471 --> 00:40:33.639
I wanted to protect you.

481
00:40:33.722 --> 00:40:36.350
By dragging us out to a place
that isn't even open for settlement?

482
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:39.228
-I didn't know that at the time.
-But you know it now!

483
00:40:40.729 --> 00:40:42.565
And you said nothing!

484
00:40:43.232 --> 00:40:46.485
-You kept me in the dark.
-The government is going to buy the land.

485
00:40:46.569 --> 00:40:49.405
-When?
-I don't know! Nobody knows!

486
00:40:51.198 --> 00:40:53.117
We have to have faith. We have to believe.

487
00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:55.744
I don't know
how much longer I can do that. Charles.

488
00:40:55.828 --> 00:40:58.539
I don't know
how much longer I can believe.

489
00:40:59.039 --> 00:41:02.960
We didn't have a choice.
We stayed because we couldn't go back.

490
00:41:15.973 --> 00:41:17.391
Maybe you can't go back.

491
00:41:19.018 --> 00:41:20.178
What's that supposed to mean?

492
00:41:23.063 --> 00:41:25.065
Caroline. what does that mean?

493
00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:29.445
Stop it! Stop fighting!

494
00:41:38.162 --> 00:41:39.538
-Mary!
-Mary?

495
00:41:40.581 --> 00:41:41.457
-Mary?
-Mary?

496
00:41:41.540 --> 00:41:42.708
Mary. sweetheart?

497
00:41:45.544 --> 00:41:46.879
Oh. she's… she's burning up.

498
00:41:49.173 --> 00:41:51.050
Mary… Mary…

498
00:41:52.305 --> 00:42:52.161
